gr.forth.ics.graph
Interface Graph.OrderManager

Enclosing interface:
Graph
public static interface Graph.OrderManager

Provides methods for reordering (in terms of iteration) the elements of a graph.

moveEdgeBefore

void moveEdgeBefore(Edge edge,
                    boolean onSourceNode,
                    Edge beforeWhat)
Moves the specified edge exactly before the target edge. These edges must exist in the same edge list, that is:
  • if onSourceNode is true, edge.n1() == beforeWhat.n1() must be true
  • if onSourceNode is false, edge.n2() == beforeWhat.n2() must be true

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - when edges do not belong to the same edge list, or they are not contained in the graph

moveEdgeAfter

void moveEdgeAfter(Edge edge,
                   boolean onSourceNode,
                   Edge afterWhat)
Moves the specified edge exactly after the target edge. These edges must exist in the same edge list, that is:
  • if onSourceNode is true, edge.n1() == beforeWhat.n1() must be true
  • if onSourceNode is false, edge.n2() == beforeWhat.n2() must be true

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - when edges do not belong to the same edge list, or they are not contained in the graph
